headline: Wells Fargo adjusts its S&P 500 sector recommendations
summary: Investing.com -- Wells Fargo has raised its U.S. growth and earnings forecasts and adjusted its sector calls, shifting preference toward Industrials, Financials, and Utilities while reducing exposure to Communications Services and Health Care.

headline: Feast or Fluke? US Home Sales Hit Highest in Almost Four Years
summary: The roaring August demand put a serious dent in the glut of new homes on the market, with inventory falling to the lowest level this year.
